</EM></STRONG>

<HR>
<H3>1995 EMPLOYMENT IN MAJOR ILLINOIS INDUSTRIES</H3>

Restaurants and fast-food establishments continue to provide employment for a large number of workers in the state.  These eating places also added a sizeable number of jobs last year with an additional 11,100 workers.  Other large classifications with noticeable gains were help (personnel) supply services with 10,800 and elementary and secondary schools with 10,200.  The fast movers, percentage-wise, were: miscellaneous business services, gaining 15.6 percent; personnel supply with a 13.3 percent growth; and department stores which added 5.8 percent more workers.<P>   

While the number of overall jobs rose last year, several large industries posted decreases due to mergers, cost-cutting and technological advances in the marketplace.  National commercial banks and trusts employment declined by 2,500, with hospitals shedding 1,600 jobs and telephone communications reducing their payrolls by 800. <P>

