<a name="Announcing Upcoming Fair Housing Workshop"><hr></a>
<h3>ANNOUNCING UPCOMING FAIR HOUSING WORKSHOP</h3>

Title VIII of the Civil Rights Act of 1968 prohibits discrimination in housing on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, or national origin.  This law also requires administration of federal programs in a manner that affirmatively furthers fair housing.  As recipients of CDAP grants, communities are obligated to pursue fair housing activities.  To help CDAP grant recipients achieve this goal, the Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs (DCCA), the Illinois Department of Human Rights (DHR),  and the Illinois Housing Development Authority (IHDA) are co-sponsoring a conference on fair housing.  The conference will detail federal rules which mandate this activity and provide insight as to how communities can pursue this goal.<p>

The conference is scheduled to be held on Tuesday, April 30, 1996, from 9:00 a.m. until 4:00 p.m., at the Holiday Inn in Decatur.  A brochure with more information on the conference along with registration instructions will be forwarded to you as we get closer to the date.  Should you have any questions on this conference, contact Jay Bales at DCCA at 217/785-6181.<p>


