<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: Just for Kids -- Coal is Cool!</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#0000A0" LINK="#0000A0" VLINK="#FF0000" ALINK="#FF0000">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>

<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4>

<h3 align=center>New Technologies</h3>
<hr>
<h4>How does coal effect the environment?</h4>

Over the past several years, scientists, coal companies and others have become concerned about the air we breathe.  They want to make sure that the harmful chemicals that are released into the air when coal is burned do not harm the environment.  Therefore, technologies wee developed to remove these chemicals from coal before, during and after it is burned.  These technologies are called clean coal technologies.  Today scientists are continuing to find ways that will enable coal to be burned cleaner.  As a result, we will have a cleaner and healthier environment.<p>


