<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Feeder Swine Dealers</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Feeder Swine Dealers
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
Bureau of Animal Health<BR>
P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9281<BR>
(217) 782-4944<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 201, 620/1-19.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required to operate as a feeder swine dealer. "Feeder Swine" means all swine except those consigned directly to slaughter or swine sold as breeding animals with negative brucellosis test. The license allows the business to sell or offer to sell feeder swine in Illinois.  Violations are a petty offense and subject to a fine of at least $200. A license is valid for one calendar year. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete Form # H-58, "Application for License as a Feeder Swine Dealer".  The licensing process usually takes about one week.  Denied applications may be appealed to the Director of Agriculture, and a hearing requested.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file with the Department a $5,000 bond or a trust fund agreement showing proof of deposits with a bank or trust company of either $5,000 in cash or securities having a fair market value of $5,000.  This license must be prominently displayed at each place of business of the feeder swine dealer.  Feeder swine originating in Illinois must bear ear-tags before being sold or commingled.<P>

Feeder swine originating outside Illinois shall bear ear tags indicating the state of origin, must arrive directly from that state, and be accompanied by a health certificate.  Every sale of out-of-state feeder swine must be reported by the dealer to the Department 	   within 7 days. Licensed feeder swine dealers must record the names and addresses of buyers and sellers, the number of swine bought and sold and ear tag numbers.  Records must be retained for 12 months.<P>

Records must be available for inspection by the Department.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Original license: $25<P>
Annual License renewal: $10<P>
License to act as agent: $5.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
