<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Meat Broker, Poultry Broker or Meat & Poultry Broker.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Meat Broker, Poultry Broker or Meat & Poultry Broker.
</DD></DL>

<HR>				
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
Bureau of Meat & Poultry Inspection / Compliance Section<BR>
State Fairgrounds, P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
(217) 785-4709<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 650/1 - 20 (The Meat & Poultry Inspection Act.)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
This license is required before any business may buy, negotiate for purchase of, handle, or take possession of  meat or poultry products for the purpose of selling or negotiating the sale of those products on commission, in their original containers without changing the character of the products in any way.  Doing business without a license from the Department is a Class A misdemeanor and may be punished by fines of up to $1,000 and/or a year in jail.  A license is valid for one year, and expires each year on June 30. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An applicant must complete and file an application with the Department. Applicants doing business under an assumed name must include proof that it is registered with the clerk of the county in which the business is located.  Corporations must include proof that it is registered with the Secretary of State's Office.   A Department Compliance Officer must inspect and approve the facility prior to licensing.
</DD></DL>

<HR>	
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The applicant must not have prior convictions of violating the Meat & Poultry Inspection Act.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The fee for the license is $50.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
