<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Mixed Fertilizer & Fertilizer Materials Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Mixed Fertilizer & Fertilizer Materials Registration
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9281<BR>
Bureau of Agricultural Products Inspection<BR>
(217) 785-8349<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
505 Illinois Compiled Statutes 80/1 et seq.  (Illinois Fertilizer Act)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Businesses (such as chemical plants, lawn supply companies and  retail stores) that distribute certain fertilizers must be registered with the Department.  Registration allows a business to distribute, store, mix, transport or use anhydrous ammonia or nitrogen solutions in the State of Illinois.  Violations are a business offense punishable by a fine not to exceed $1,000.  Registration is valid for one year.  All registrations expire on December 31.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
To register,  applicants must complete and file with the Department the appropriate forms:  IL406-0005 - "Application for Registration of Custom Mix Fertilizer" IL406-0006 - "Application for Registrtion-Commercial Fertilizer- 5# Package or More" IL406-0007- "Application for Registration-Specialty Fertilizer - Less than 5# Package".<P>

Applications for registration must contain information including the net weight, brand and grade, guaranteed analysis, and applicant's name and address, and a label for each product to be registered.  Approval usually takes about 3 weeks.  Applications are denied if the material does not conform to the label description.  If denied, the process is subject to the Administrative Review Law.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The plant nutrient content of each and every commercial fertilizer must remain uniform for the period of registration.  The label must be affixed to the fertilizer container and must be clearly legible.  Bulk fertilizer must be accompanied by a printed statement with label information.  The applicant must allow access for inspection of product and facilities during business hours.  Distribution and storage facilities must comply with local zoning ordinance requirements.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Product registration fee is $5 per product per year.<P>

The inspection fee on fertilizer in units over 5# is $.20/ton.<P>

The annual inspection fee on individual packages of 5# or less is $25 for each product.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
