<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Treatment and Intervention (DUI, BASSET) Licenses.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>

<DL><DD>Treatment and Intervention (DUI, BASSET) Licenses.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>

<DL><DD> Illinois Department of Alcoholism & Substance Abuse<BR>
               222 South College St., Second Floor<BR>
               Springfield, IL 62704-1875<BR>
               Division of Licensing & Monitoring<BR>
               (217) 782-0685<BR></DD></DL>
          
<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>20 Illinois Compiled Statutes 305/4</DD></DL>

<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>Title 77, Illinois Administrative Code, Section 2056, 2058.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>

<DL><DD>DASA issues the following licenses for
persons engaged in the treatment and intervention activities (specified in
the Illinois Administrative Code Section 2056 and 2058):  1.)  Treatment
Licenses (for individuals addicted to or abusing alcohol of other drugs).
2.)  Intervention Licenses (for professional evaluations of DUI offenders,
for remedial education courses for DUI offenders and for businesses to
provide beverage alcohol sellers education and training (BASSET) programs).
If the Department determines that an unlicensed person and or program (or
other entity) is engaging in activities that require any of these licenses,
the Director will issue an order requiring that person, program or entity
to cease operations.  The recipient of the order has ten (10) days to
support a claim that a license is not required.  Failure to do so will
result in referral of the matter to the appropriate State's Attorney or
Office of the Attorney General for prosecution.  Licenses are effective for
two (2) years.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>

<DL><DD>Application forms are available from Department.  The
average processing time for an application is less than thirty (30) days.
Common reasons for denying a license are incomplete applications and
failure to submit fees</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>

<DL><DD>An application for renewal of a license must be submitted no less than 30 days prior to
expiration of the current license.  If a licensed business changes
ownership or location, a license becomes null and void and a new license
must be applied for.  The Department has the right to conduct random
inspections of facilities to insure compliance with the regulations or
requirements of each license.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>

<DL><DD>1.  The fee for application for a license is $200.<P>
2.  The fee for application renewal of a license is $200.

 No fee shall be required of any unit of local, State or Federal government</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
