<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Telecommunication Service: Certificate of Convenience and Necessity or Certificate of Authority for Operation of a Public Utilities</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Telecommunication Service: Certificate of Convenience and Necessity or Certificate of Authority for Operation of a Public Utilities
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Commerce Commission<BR>
527 East Capitol, P.O. Box 19280<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9280<BR>
Public Utilities Division/Telecommunications Department<BR>
(217) 524-5060<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
220 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/13-401 and 13-405.  (Public Utilities Act) 
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
83 Illinois Administrative Code Part 200 (Rules of Practice)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Certificate of Public Convenience and Necessity or Certificate of Authority ("Certificate") allows a telecommunications carrier to provide local exchange or interexchange service. Certificates remain effective until the service is deemed no longer necessary to the public convenience.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for a Certificate must file a petition with the Commission,  following the process described in its "Rules of Practice".  Upon receipt of the petition, the Commission will conduct a public hearing and, if it determines that the applicant possesses sufficient technical, financial and managerial expertise and ability to provide service, may grant a Certificate.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for a Certificate have the legal burden of proving to the Commission that it possesses sufficient technical, financial and managerial resources and abilities to provide service.  <P>

A Public Utility must pay an annual regulatory tax at 0.1% on gross revenues. <P>

Public Utilities must file an annual report.<P>

Public utilities must file tariffs, or any changes in its tariffs, with the Commission before providing service. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
There are no fees for a Certificate.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
