<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Required Chemical Safety Contingency Plan</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile: </H3>

	<DL><DD>Required Chemical Safety Contingency Plan</DD></DL>

<HR>                    
<H3>II.  Agency: </H3>

<DL><DD>Illinois Environmental Protection Agency (IEPA)<BR>
Illinois Emergency Management Agency (IEMA)</DD></DL>

<DL><DD><PRE>Office of Chemical Safety
2200 Churchill Rd.                      110 East Adams Street
Springfield, IL 62706                   Springfield, IL 62701
(217) 785-0830                          (217) 782-7860</PRE></DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>

<DL><DD>430 Illinois Compiled Statutes 45/1.   (Illinois Chemical Safety Act)</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>

<DL><DD><P>Businesses covered by the SIC codes* listed below must file with local fire, police or other emergency agency, an
emergency plan (Plan) to deal with off-site releases involving chemicals
and oil, or their impact.  Facilities subject to this law are businesses
with five or more full-time employees or 20 or more part-time employees, or
any business facility that is determined by the Agency to pose a threat to
the environment or public health. Facilities subject to this requirement
are required to prepare Chemical Safety Contingency Plans that meet the
minimum criteria specified in the Law.  Any business that operates without
a contingency plan may be liable for a fine of up to $10,000 for each
violation, plus $1,000 for each day the violation continues.

<P>*The  SIC codes covered are:

  <DL> <DD> <PRE>     2295           2842           2911           3471
     2491           2851           2952           4953
     2671-2         2865           2999           5085
     2812-3         2869           3081-9         5162
     2819           2873-4         3111           5169
     2821           2879           3339           5171-2
     2834           2891-2         3432</PRE></DD></DL></DD></DL>
     
<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process: </H3>

<DL><DD>No initial approval is required.  Agency may conduct inspections to assure plans exist.  The Agency also may call in
plans for review if it determines that a "significant" off-site emergency
release has occurred.  The Agency or IEMA may require correction of any
deficiency that it identifies in a Plan.</DD></DL>

<HR>     
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>

<DL><DD>Contingency Emergency Plans must be updated each year.  Employee training in
implementation of the Plan also is required.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>

<DL><DD>None.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
