<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Federal Contractor Job Listings</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3> I.   Business Requirement Profile:
</H3><DL><DD>
Federal Contractor Job Listings
             </DD></DL><HR><H3>
II.  Agency:</H3><DL><DD>     Illinois Department of Employment Security<BR>
               Job Service Programs<BR>
               401 South State Street  3-S<BR>
               Chicago, Illinois 60605        <BR>
               (312) 793-6801                     <BR></DD></DL><HR>
                                                                <H3>
III. Statute: </H3><DL><DD>
Title 38 United States Code, Ch. 41, Section 4212(a) as amended, 38 USC  4212(a)
                           </DD></DL><H3>
     Regulation:</H3><DL><DD>  41 Code of Federal Regulation 60-250, effective January 5, 1995
                             </DD></DL><HR><H3>
IV.  Requirement Description: </H3><DL><DD>Illinois businesses with United States government contracts of $10,000 or more must list job openings with the Illinois Department of Employment Security (IDES). Those employers must take affirmative action to employ, and advance in employment, qualified, disabled veterans and veterans of the Vietnam era.

Each business with a government contract or subcontract for $50,000 or more and having at least 50 employees, is required to prepare and maintain an affirmative action program that sets forth the policies and practices in hiring and promoting qualified disabled and Vietnam era veterans. The plan must be updated each year.  The program may be separated from or integrated into other affirmative action programs.

Employers must list with the appropriate IDES office existing bona fide job openings that are available during the performance of the contract. Openings not generated by the contract, or occurring at an establishment other than the one wherein the contract is being performed, are included.

Failure to comply may result in a penalties including a fine and/or loss of a contract.
                                           </DD></DL><HR><H3>
V.   Approval Process:</H3><DL><DD>  An employer may call, fax or write any of IDES statewide local offices to list a job order.  The job order should contain the requirements to successfully perform the job duties, such as the minimum experience, skills, aptitudes and education required. 

The job is properly classified by assigning a job title.  

The Department conducts a follow-up to insure that the order is properly serviced.  

The Department maintains contact with employers to inform them of actions taken or if changes to the order are appropriate.  

Orders are promptly closed when jobs are filled or canceled.
                                   </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3><DL><DD>  None
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
VII. Fees:</H3><DL><DD>  None
                       </DD></DL>





