<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Currency Exchange License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Currency Exchange License
</dd></dl><hr>
<h3>II. Agency:</h3>
<dl><dd>
Department of Financial Institutions<br>
Currency Exchange Division<br>
100 West Randolph Street, Suite 15-700<br>
Chicago, IL 60601<br>
(312) 814-5153 <br>
</dd></dl><hr>

<h3>III. Statute:</h3>
<dl><dd>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes 405/.1 (Currency Exchange Act) 
</dd></dl><hr>
<h3>IV. Requirement Description:</h3>
<dl><dd>
This license is required for businesses that offer as their primary service the cashing of checks and selling money orders for a fee as well as engaging in other activities provided in the Act. Licenses are valid for one year and may be renewed.  A separate license is required for each location. <p>
</dd></dl><hr>
<h3>V. Approval Process:</h3>
<dl><dd>
Each currency exchange owner, officer, stockholder and/or director must submit a license application to the Department. Applications must include financial data for the new exchange.  On the basis of a "Need of Community" statement, the Department will assess whether the community needs the proposed currency exchange and the effect it will have on the financial stability of existing currency exchanges. Applicants also must submit other documents including a completed Department questionnaire, personal financial statement and a credit bureau report. Failure to have a valid "Need of Community" statement is a common reason for denial. Applications are usually processed within 90 days. Denied applications may be appealed. </dd></dl><hr>

<h3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites: </h3>
<dl>
<dt><strong>Co-Requisites:</strong><dd> Applicants have a loan commitment.  <p>

<dt><strong>Post requisites: </strong><dd> License holders are required to file an annual report and a bond with the Department. Applicants also must comply with the Currency Exchange Act.<p>
</dl><hr>

<h3>VII. Fees:</h3>
<dl><dd><dl>
<dt>Application/Investigation fee  <dd> $500
<dt>Change of Location fee  <dd>        $150 
<dt>Annual license fee   <dd>           $200 (Community Currency Exchange)
                        <dd>  $ 25 (Ambulatory Currency Exchange)
</dl></dl>






