<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Financial Planning & Management Services License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Financial Planning & Management Services License
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>II. Agency:
</H3><dl><dd>
Department of Financial Institutions<BR>
Consumer Credit Division<BR>
500 Iles Park Place; Suite 500<BR>
Springfield, IL 62718<BR>
(217) 782-3704<BR>
</dd></dl><hr>

<H3>III. Statute:
</H3><dl><dd>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes 665 
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:
</H3><dl><dd>
A license is required to conduct business as a financial planner or manager*. Conducting financial planning and management services without a license a Class B misdemeanor.  Contracts for financial planning or managing with an unlicensed person are null & void and of no legal effect. Cotracts between license holders and individuals must be in writing and state fees and charges.  More than one license may be issued to the same person for separate places of business, and separate licenses are required for each business location. Licenses are valid for a maximum of 1 year and expire on January 1.  <P>

Applications to renew a license must be filed by December 1 each year.  <P>

*(Financial planning means the planning and management of the financial affairs of an individual and distribution of money to his or her creditors, or acting as an individual's agent by distributing his or her income to creditors whether a fee is charged for such services or not. The title does not apply to attorneys, banks, judicial officers and others defined by the statute.)<P></dd></dl><hr>

<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3><dl><dd>

Applications must be submitted on forms provided by the Department and be accompanied by appropriate fees, a $7,500 bond, a credit report and a financial statement. Upon receipt of an application and fees, applicant will be investigated as to financial responsibility, experience, character and general fitness, and whether applicant has been convicted of a crime involving moral turpitude or default of payment of money collected for others.  Applications are usually processed within 30 days.  Anyone denied a license will be notified by mail and given 60 days to respond to the denial.<P></dd></dl><hr>

<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites:</H3>
<dl><dd>
License holders must maintain records and accounts including receipts for payments he or she receives, and files showing the amounts paid to creditors for individuals contracting with the license holder.  Licensees must keep in the file for each debtor a written analysis of debtor's income and expenses to substantiate that the plan of payment is feasible and practical.  
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>VII. Fees:
</H3><dl><dd><dl>
<dt>Annual License Fee:      <dd>    $100
<dt>Initial Investigation Fee:  <dd> $ 35
<dt>Relocation Fee:      <dd>        $ 10
<dt>Name Change:             <dd>    $ 10
</dl></dl>





<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
