<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Illinois State Chartered Credit Unions</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:
</H3><dl><dd>
Illinois State Chartered Credit Unions
</dd></dl><HR>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Illinois Department of Financial Institutions<BR>
Credit Union Division<BR>
100 West Randolph, Suite 15-700<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<BR>
(312)  814-2010 <BR>
</dd></dl><hr>

<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<dl><dd>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes 305/1 (Illinois Credit Union Act) 
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<dl><dd>
A charter is required to operate as an Illinois State Chartered Credit Union.  A State Chartered Credit Union is a non-profit, nine or more member-owned cooperative financial institution, incorporated for the purpose of encouraging thrift among its members, creating a source of credit at a reasonable rate and providing an opportunity for its members to improve their economic and social conditions.   <P>
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Applications must be submitted to the Department, with additional information including resumes of all proposed members of the board of directors, a completed Articles of Incorporation form,  a detailed business plan and feasibility study, collection, lending and investment policies and staffing of the credit union, the goals of proposed dividend rates paid on members' share accounts, and evidence of a commitment for share insurance.  The Department provides written notice of the Director's decision based upon review of the application. <P></dd></dl><hr>

<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites:</H3>
<dl>
<dt><STRONG>Pre-Requisites</STRONG><dd>  Applicants must file a Certificate of Approval with the Articles of Incorporation attached, together with applicable fees, in the office of  the County Recorder (or, if there is no County Recorder, in the office of the County Clerk) of the County where the credit union proposes to locate its principal place of business.  Once the documents are properly filed and recorded, the credit union is incorporated under this Act. <p>

<dt><STRONG>Post-Requisites</STRONG><dd> A credit union that is granted a charter must comply with provisions and requirements of the Illinois Credit Union Act and Rules and Regulations as promulgated by the Director of the Department of Financial Institutions. <P></dl><hr>

<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
There is a $25 application processing fee. Credit unions examined by the Department also must pay an examination fee based upon total assets on the date of examination, as shown in a "Statement of Condition". <P>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
