<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Riverboat Owners License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Riverboat Owners License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Gaming Board / Department of Revenue<BR>
Enforcement Division<BR>
160 North LaSalle St., 3rd floor<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 814-4700<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
230 Illinois Revised Statutes 10/1
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 80, Illinois Administrative Code, Part 3000.100
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An Owners License is required to conduct a riverboat gambling operation.
Licenses are valid for one year and may be renewed if the Board determines
the License holder is suitable for license renewal.  Only 10 licenses are
available.  Applicants only may obtain a license upon Board approval when
either statutes are amended to allow more licenses or upon failure or
revocation of an existing license.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must first submit an "Owner's Application Form" after which the
Board will conduct a background investigation.  The applicant must also
submit all documents, resolutions, and letters of support from the
municipal or county government where the Licensed riverboat will dock.
Processing time for applications varies according to the time required for
the background investigation.  Reasons for denial of an application include
conduct by the licensee considered to be in violation of the Act and rules
established by the Board.  If an application is denied applicant may
request a hearing.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must disclose the identity of every person, association, trust,
or corporation having a greater than 1% direct or indirect interest in the
riverboat gambling operation with respect to which license is sold.
Applicants must submit a file stamped copy of the $200,000 performance bond
to the Board.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<PRE>
Application Fee:                 	 	  $50,000
License Fee for 1st year of operation:            $25,000
License Fee for succeeding years of operation:    $ 5,000
</PRE>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
