<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: The Illinois Child Labor Law  </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The Illinois Child Labor Law  
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Labor<BR>
Fair Labor Standards Division<BR>
160 N. LaSalle<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601 <BR>
(312) 793-2804<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
820 Illinois Compiled Statutes 205
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The Act prohibits minors under 16 from working for an employer without a certificate from the Department. A certificate allows the employment of  a minor during school vacation or outside school hours. Employment of a minor under the age of 16 without a certificate issued by the Department is a Class A Misdemeanor and may be punished by fines of up to $5,000 per violation.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A certificate is required before a minor may work for an employer.  Certificates must be signed by the Issuing Officer and a copy must be filed with the Department. Certificates will be issued upon receipt of a written, in-person application by the minor desiring employment, accompanied by a parent, guardian or custodian. Applications must include a statement of intention to employ signed by a prospective employer, evidence of age, showing the minor's age (by birth certificate or similar document), a statement on the Department form, signed by the minor's school principal, the minor's name, address, and a statement of physical fitness signed by an examining doctor or  public health doctor. Work considered too hazardous for minors under 16 are described specifically in the Act. The Department will conduct a hearing to revoke a certificate upon receipt of a written complaint alleging violation of this act. Orders of the Department may be appealed to the circuit court.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A new employment certificate is required  each year for a minor under 16. Employers must keep records of minor's employment including: The hours worked each day and each week, the starting and ending times of work and records of lunch breaks (both scheduled and actual times).<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
