<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Liquor Licenses for the following categories (Distribution):  Distributor's License, Non-Resident Dealer's License, Importing Distributor's License, Foreign Importer's License.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Liquor Licenses for the following categories (Distribution):  Distributor's License, Non-Resident Dealer's License, Importing Distributor's License, Foreign Importer's License.
</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Liquor Control Commission<BR>
Licensing Unit<BR>
100 West Randolph, Suite 5-300<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<BR>
312/ 814-2206<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
235 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/5-1	(Illinois Liquor Control Act)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>

<DL><DD>
Licenses for the categories listed above each have a brief definition provided on the front page of their respective "Application Instruction Sheet."  Each individual business involved in the sale of alcoholic beverages  requires a separate license.<P>

Licenses are valid for one (1) year.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Interested parties must complete and file a standard form, Application for License (Form# IL567-0015) or Application for Non-Resident Dealer's License (Form #82-2), for the licenses listed above. Applicants are invited to call the Commission for assistance. The Commission will send a set of instructions to assist the applicant with completion of the form. The Commission requires additional forms for certain licenses, and will include all necessary forms for each category. If the Commission's licensing staff determines that more information is required, or that the application is incomplete, they will return the forms to the applicant for further information. Denied applications may be revised and resubmitted to the Commission.  Processing generally takes 2-3 weeks.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisities & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License applications must include a one thousand dollar ($1,000.00) Liquor Gallonage Tax Bond (Form# ECS-74) to be submitted to the Illinois Department of Revenue for approval. This form is provided by the Illinois Liquor Control Commission.<P> 

In addition, applications must include Registration Statement(s) (IL567-0014) and a copy of the Federal Label Approval which comes from the U. S. Department of Treasury, Bureau of Alcohol Tobacco & Firearms (BATF).<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<PRE>
A.)  Distributor's License					$270.00
B.)  Non-Resident Dealer's License (>500,000 Gallons)	        $270.00
C.)  Non-Resident Dealer's License  (<500,000 gallons)		$ 90.00
D.)  Importing Distributor's License				$ 25.00
E.)  Foreign Importer's License					$ 25.00
</PRE>
</DD></DL>
<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
