<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Liquor Licenses for the following categories (Manufacturers): Distiller, Rectifier, Brewer, First-Class Wine Manufacturer, Second-Class Wine Manufacturer, First-Class Winemaker, Second-Class Winemaker, and Limited Wine Manufacturer.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>

<DL>
<DD>Liquor Licenses for the following categories (Manufacturers): Distiller, Rectifier, Brewer, First-Class Wine Manufacturer, Second-Class Wine Manufacturer, First-Class Winemaker, Second-Class Winemaker, and Limited Wine Manufacturer.</DD>
</DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. Agency: </H3>
<DL>
<DD>Illinois Liquor Control Commission<BR>
Licensing Unit<BR>
100 West Randolph, Suite 5-300<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<BR>
312/ 814-2206</DD>
</DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>

<DL>
<DD>235 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/5-1 (Illinois Liquor Control Act)</DD>
</DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL>
<DD>Licenses for the categories listed above each have a brief definition provided on the front page of their respective "Application Instruction Sheet."  Each individual business involved in the manufacture or importation of alcoholic beverages requires a separate license.<P>

Licenses are valid for one (1) year.</DD>
</DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<DL>
<DD>Interested parties must complete and file a standard form, Application for License (Form# IL567-0015), for all licenses listed above.  Applicants are invited to call the Commission for assistance.  The Commission will send a set of instructions to assist the applicant with completion of the form.  The Commission requires additional forms for certain licenses, and will include all necessary forms for each category.  If the Commission's licensing staff determines that more information is required, or that the application is incomplete, they will return the forms to the applicant for further information.  Denied applications may be revised and resubmitted to the Commission.  Processing generally takes 2-3 weeks.</DD>
</DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisities & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL>
<DD>License applications must include a one thousand dollar ($1,000.00) Liquor Gallonage Tax Bond (Form# ECS-74) to be submitted to the Illinois Department of Revenue for approval.  This form is provided by the Illinois Liquor Control Commission.</DD><P>

<DD>In addition, applications must include Registration Statement(s) (IL567-0014) and a copy of the Federal Label Approval which comes from the U. S. Department of Treasury, Bureau of Alcohol Tobacco & Firearms (BATF).</DD><P>
</DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>

<PRE>
	A.)  Distiller				       $3,600.00
	B.)  Rectifier				       $3,600.00
	C.)  Brewer				       $  900.00
	D.)  First-Class Wine Manufacturer             $  600.00
	E.)  Second-Class Wine Manufacturer            $1,200.00
	F.)  First-Class Winemaker		       $  240.00
	G.)  Second-Class Winemaker	               $  480.00
	H.)  Limited Wine Manufacturer	               $  120.00
</PRE>

