<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Liquor Licenses for the following categories (Miscellaneous):  Auction Liquor License,  Broker's License, Non-Beverage User's License.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Liquor Licenses for the following categories (Miscellaneous):  Auction Liquor License,  Broker's License, Non-Beverage User's License.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Liquor Control Commission<BR>
Licensing Unit<BR>
100 West Randolph, Suite 5-300<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<BR>
(312) 814-2206<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>	
<DL><DD>
235 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/5-1	(Illinois Liquor Control Act)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Licenses for the categories listed above each have a brief definition provided on the front page of their respective "Application Instruction Sheet." Each individual business involved in the sale of alcoholic beverages requires a separate license.<P>

Licenses are valid for one (1) year.  Non-Beverage User's Licenses are valid until the amount of alcohol authorized to be purchased with the license has been exhausted.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Interested parties must complete and file a standard form, Application for License (Form# IL567-0015), or an Application For A Non-Beverage User's License (Form# IL567-0027),  for the licenses listed above. Applicants are invited to call the Commission for assistance. The Commission will send a set of instructions to assist the applicant with completion of the form. The Commission requires additional forms for certain licenses, and will include all necessary forms for each category. If the Commission's licensing staff determines that more information is required, or that the application is incomplete, they will return the forms to the applicant for further information. Denied applications may be revised and resubmitted to the Commission.  Processing generally takes 2-3 weeks.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisities & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<PRE>
A.)  Auction Liquor License			$600.00<P>
B.)  Broker's Liquor License			$600.00<P>
C.)  Non-Beverage User's License<P>
                  Class 1     $ 24.00
                  Class 2     $ 60.00
                  Class 3     $120.00
                  Class 4     $240.00
                  Class 5     $600.00

</PRE>
<DD></DL>

