<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Liquor Licenses for the following categories (Passenger Carriers):  Airplane License, Boat License, Railroad License.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL>
<DD>Liquor Licenses for the following categories (Passenger Carriers):  Airplane License, Boat License, Railroad License.</DD>
</DL>
<HR>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Liquor Control Commission<BR>
Licensing Unit<BR>
100 West Randolph, Suite 5-300<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<BR>
(312) 814-2206<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>	

<DL><DD>235 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/5-1 (Illinois Liquor Control Act)</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL>
<DD>Licenses for the categories listed above each have a brief definition provided on the front page of their respective "Application Instruction Sheet."  Each individual business involved in the sale of alcoholic beverages on passenger planes, railcars, or boats requires a separate license for each railcar, boat, or plane on which alcohol is sold or served.</DD><P>

<DD>Licenses are valid for one (1) year.</DD><P>
</DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<DL>
<DD>Interested parties must complete and file a standard form, Application for License (Form# IL567-0015), for all licenses listed above.  Applicants are invited to call the Commission for assistance. The Commission will send a set of instructions to assist the applicant with completion of the form. The Commission requires additional forms for certain licenses, and will include all necessary forms for each category. If the Commission's licensing staff determines that more information is required, or that the application is incomplete, they will return the forms to the applicant for further information. Denied applications may be revised and resubmitted to the Commission. Processing generally takes 2-3 weeks.</DD>
</DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisities & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL>
<PRE>
<DD>A.)  Airplane				     $ 60.00  (per aircraft)</DD>
<DD>B.)  Boat				     $180.00  (per boat)</DD>
<DD>C.)  Railroad				     $ 60.00  (per railcar)</DD>
</PRE>
</DL>

