<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop:  Illinois Lottery Agent License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<P><H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD> Illinois Lottery Agent License</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II. Agency: <P></H3>
<DL><DD>Department of the Lottery ("Lottery")<BR>
Marketing Division<BR>
201 E. Madison<BR>
Springfield, IL 62702<BR>
(217) 524-5241 or (800) 252-1775<P></DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3><DL><DD> 20 Illinois Compiled Statutes 1605/10<P></DD></DL>
<H3><DD> Regulation:</DD></H3><DL><DD> Title 11, Illinois Administrative Code: 1770.20<P></DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description</H3>

<DL><DD>A license is required before any business may
sell Illinois Lottery tickets. Licenses are issued for a two year period.
Any Illinois business may apply for a license.<P>

a)  A business will not be licensed to act solely as a Lottery agent.<P>

b)  A license will not be issued to a business if an owner, officer,
managing agent, or any person or entity having an interest in the business
of 5% or more has a record of conviction for a felony, fraud,
misrepresentation, or gambling, or has been a professional gambler.
Convicted felons may be considered if ten (10) years have elapsed since
completion of sentencing, all conditions of probation, conditional
discharge, etc. have been met, there has been no subsequent criminal
activity and the applicant furnishes at least three (3) letters from
responsible members of the community attesting to his or her good
character.<P>

c)  The business and its owners or partners must be in compliance with all
Illinois Department of Revenue tax laws.<P>

d)  All owners/officers of the business must be 18 years of age
or older.<P>

Selling Illinois Lottery tickets without a license is a Class B misdemeanor
for first offenders, and a Class 4 felony for subsequent offenses.<P>
</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>

<DL><DD>Applicants must file an "Agent Contract for Sale of Lottery Tickets" (Form No. IDL-30/IL458-0081) and the appropriate fee with
the Lottery.  Upon receipt, the Lottery will schedule a visit by a Lottery
Representative to evaluate the business, its principals and location.<P>

If  the Representative does not recommend a site for licensing, the
applicant is notified in writing and the application fee is returned.  If
the Representative recommends the business for a license, the Illinois
State Police and the Illinois Department of Revenue will conduct an
investigation of the applicant.<P>

The Lottery may issue a license and schedule agents for Lottery sales
training if the investigations are satisfactory and the applicants have
acceptable credit history, or (in the event of poor credit history) post a
security deposit.<P>

If a license is denied due to unacceptable criminal, tax or credit history,
the applicant is notified in writing and may petition for an administrative
hearing.<P>

Lottery rules require applications be approved or denied within 180 days of
receipt of the application and fee, but most applications are processed
within 60 days of receipt.<P></DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>

<DL><DD>Licensed Agents are required by law to establish and maintain a separate
bank account for deposit of Lottery sales proceeds (separate and apart from
other business funds).<P>

Licensed agents must provide periodic ticket settlement reports, and
deposit the amount due to the Department in the agent's Lottery account
prior to scheduled electronic funds transfer to the Department of the
Lottery.<P>

Additional reports may be required by special circumstances.<P><DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3><P>

<DL><DD>One-time license application fee:  $10.00</DD>
<DD>Weekly on-line charge:             $ 5.00</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
