<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Authority to Amend a Class II Injection Well Permit </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Authority to Amend a Class II Injection Well Permit 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Office Mines & Minerals (OMM)<BR>
Oil & Gas Division<BR>
524 South Second Street<BR>
Springfield, IL 62701-1787<BR>
(217) 782-7756<BR>
TDD:  (217) 524-4626<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 725/6
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
62 Illinois Administrative Code 240 C 240.390
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Authorization is required to change the injection interval in a permitted Class II Injection Well.<P>

Failure to comply may result in enforcement action, including civil penalties.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit a second "Class II Injection Well Permit" application, form #OG-4, together with additional information described on the back of the application and proof of public notice to offset operations. <P>

If an objection is received by OMM, a hearing may be held to resolve the objection. <P>

Review, approval and permit to amend generally takes 30 to 60 days depending upon whether any additional information is required by OMM. <P>

Department decisions are subject to administrative review. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file a "Well Completion Report", form #OG-9; a "Tubing & Packer Report", form #OG-13, and; a "Mechanical Integrity Report", from #OG-23 to OMM<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
There is a $100 non-refundable application fee.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
