<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Fee Fishing Area License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3> I.   Business Requirement Profile:
    </H3><DL><DD>
Fee Fishing Area License
                 </DD></DL><HR><H3>
II.  Agency:                       </H3>
                                        <DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Conservation Division                       <BR>
Fee Fishing Area License Unit                   <BR>
524 S. 2nd Street, Room 210                         <BR>
P. O. Box 19458                                         <BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9458                                  <BR>
(217) 785-3423                                                  <BR>
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
III. Statute:     </H3>
                       <DL><DD>
515 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/20 to 95.
                               </DD></DL><HR><H3>
IV.  Requirement Description:                    </H3>
                                                      <DL><DD>
A license is required before anyone who owns, controls or operates a water area used for fishing, or controls access to the water area, may charge a fee (directly or indirectly) to allow fishing at the water area.  

Fee Fishing Area Licenses are issued for a period of up to one year and are valid from February 1, and expire the following  January 31.
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
V.   Approval Process:</H3>
                           <DL><DD>
Applicants must complete and file with the Department a "Fee Fishing Area License Application", together with the requisite fee.  

Applications require approval by a Department biologist before a license may be issued.  Licenses are issued within approximately 2 weeks after receipt of an application by the Department.
                                   </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites:</H3>
                                                          <DL><DD>
None.</DD></DL>
<HR><H3>
VII. Fees:
        </H3><DL><DD>
$50 annually.        <P>

Make checks or money orders payable to the Department of Natural Resources.
                        </DD></DL>






