<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Passenger Boat License and Rental Boat License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3> I.   Business Requirement Profile:
               </H3><DL><DD>
Passenger Boat License and Rental Boat License
                            </DD></DL><HR><H3>
II.  Agency:                                  </H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Conservation Division                       <BR>
Passenger Boat License or Rental Boat License   <BR>
P. O. Box 19226                                     <BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9226                              <BR>
(217) 785-3429                                              <BR>
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
III. Statute:     </H3>
                       <DL><DD>
625 Illinois Compiled Statutes 45/7-1 to 7-10. 
                               </DD></DL><HR><H3>
IV.  Requirement Description:                    </H3>
                                                      <DL><DD><DL>
<DT>Passenger Boat  License:<DD>  A license is required for any person to engage in the business of operating a boat or boats carrying passengers for hire.   

<DT>Rental Boat License:<DD> A license is required for any person to engage in the business of renting a boat or boats for hire.
                            </DL>
Both licenses are issued for a maximum period of one year and expire annually on March 1.
                                 </DD></DL><HR><H3>
V.   Approval Process:                             </H3>
                                                        <DL><DD>
A Passenger Boat License will be issued by the Department upon receipt of a completed and signed Passenger Boat License Application together with the appropriate fees. (Illinois law prohibits engaging in the business of operating a boat to carry passengers for hire without a license to do so.)    

A Rental Boat License will be issued by the Department upon receipt of a completed and signed Rental Boat License Application together with appropriate fees. (Illinois law prohibits any person from engaging in the business of renting a boat for hire without a license to do so.)
 </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites:</H3>
                                                          <DL><DD>
Licenses for Passenger Boats must be prominently displayed upon the watercraft and available for inspection at all times. Licenses are issued within approximately 1 week after an application is received by the Department.
</DD></DL><HR><H3>                                                                  
VII. Fees:        </H3>
                       <DL><DD>
Annual Passenger Boat License: $50<BR>

Rental Boat License:  Annual license fee per boat is $30, plus: <DL>
      <DD>$1.00 for each boat less than 16 feet long, 
      <DD>$2.00 for each boat 16 feet, but less than 26 feet long,
      <DD>$8.00 for each boat 26 feet long or longer.
          </DL>
Make check or money order payable to Illinois Department of Natural Resources.
               </DD></DL>





