<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Permit for drilling, deepening, or converting a well, or re-entering a plugged well, in order to operate the well as an oil or gas production well or  production related well.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Permit for drilling, deepening, or converting a well, or re-entering a plugged well, in order to operate the well as an oil or gas production well or  production related well.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Office of Mines & Minerals  (OMM)<BR>
Oil & Gas Division<BR>
Springfield, IL 62701-1787<BR>
(217) 782-7756<BR>
TDD:  (217) 524-4626<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 725/6
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
62 Illinois Administrative Code 240 B 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Permit is required to drill, deepen, or convert a well for oil or gas production or water supply. Permits remain effective until the well is plugged or repermitted for another purpose.<P>

The purpose of the Permit requirements is to protect groundwater from contamination.<P>

Failure to comply with Permit requirements may result in enforcement action and fines.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit a "Well Permit Application", form #OG-10, as well as a copy of the oil and gas lease to the OMM.  Applicants must own the right to drill and produce oil from the proposed well.<P>

The location of the proposed well must meet spacing requirements of oil and gas rules. <P>

The number of wells per acre is limited based on the zone of production. <P>

Review, approval and permit issuance generally takes 3 to 5. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A $2,500 Individual or Blanket $25,000; $50,000 or $100,000 Surety Bond is required of new operators. <P>

Applicants must file a "Well Completion Report", form #OG-9, and a "Well Drilling Report", form #OG-5. <P>

Applicants may be required to submit drill cuttings (analyzed rock samples from the well) and drilling logs to the  State Geological Survey. <P>

A "Temporary Abandonment Form", form #OG-15, is also required to be submitted if the well is to be temporarily abandoned. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A $100 non-refundable application fee is required.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
