<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Permit for the Drilling of Coal Test Holes, Mineral Test Holes, Structure Test Holes, & Mineral Ground Water Monitoring Test Holes</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Permit for the Drilling of Coal Test Holes, Mineral Test Holes, Structure Test Holes, & Mineral Ground Water Monitoring Test Holes
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Office of Mines & Minerals  (OMM)<BR>
Oil & Gas Division<BR>
524 South Second Street<BR>
Springfield, Il 62701-1787<BR>
(217)782-7756<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 725/2
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
62 Illinois Administrative Code 240 L
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Permit and bond are required to drill coal, mineral, or structure test holes, or mineral groundwater monitoring test holes. Each permit covers one section of land for one Year. <P>

A single Permit authorizes an unlimited number of test holes per section. <P>

Failure to obtain a permit for drilling a test hole will result in enforcement action including<P>

revocation of the permit and assessment of a civil penalty. <P>

A Permit is valid for 1 year for drilling activities within the permitted area.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit an "Application for a Test Hole Permit", Form #OG-7 for each section of land to be drilled. <P>

Review, approval and permit issuance generally takes 3 to 5 days from the date the application was received. <P>

Department decisions are subject to administrative review.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A $2,500 Individual  or Blanket $25,000 test well surety bond is required. <P>

If Individual Bonds are submitted, a separate bond is required for each permit.<P>

Blanket Bonds apply to the entire State for an unlimited number of test holes.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A non-refundable application fee of $100 per permit is required.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
