<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Permit for the Transportation (by tank truck) of Liquid Oilfield Wastes  </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Permit for the Transportation (by tank truck) of Liquid Oilfield Wastes  
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Office of Mines & Minerals<BR>
Oil & Gas Division<BR>
524 South Second Street<BR>
Springfield, IL 62701-1787<BR>
(217) 782-7756<BR>
TDD:  (217) 524-4626<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 725/8C
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
62 Illinois Administrative Code 240 I
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Permit is required for a company to operate a liquid oilfield waste hauling operation.<P>

Each company truck (tank) also must have a Permit. <P>

Operating a tank vehicle to haul liquid oilfield waste without a permit may result in revocation of the transportation system (or company) Permit and civil penalties. <P>

Permits are valid for 2 years.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file form #OG-16, "Application for Liquid Oilfield Waste Transportation System" and form #OG-16A, "Application for Liquid Oilfield Waste Tank Permit". <P>

During the review process of the application, individual tank trucks are inspected by OMM for leaks, and a report is filed. After the report is filed, a final application review is conducted. This process takes approximately 3 to 5 days. <P>

Department decisions are subject to administrative review.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The company, or transportation system, must have a Permit to haul liquid oilfield waste before an application may be filed for vehicle, or tank, Permits.<P>

The system operator (permittee) must file with the Department a "Liquid Oilfield Waste Transportation Bond" ($10,000). <P>

Records of material received/transported must be maintained by the operator of liquid oilfield waste transportation system for a period of 3 years. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A non-refundable application fee of $100 is required for each system permit. <P>

A non-refundable application fee of $100 is required for each tank permit.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
