<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Certification of persons performing Industrial Radiography</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Certification of persons performing Industrial Radiography
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Nuclear Safety<BR>
Office of Radiation Safety / Division of Electronic Products<BR>
1035 Outer Park Dr.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62704<BR>
(217) 785-9913<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
420 Illinois Compiled Statutes 40/7a.  Radiation Protection Act of 1990.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 32, Illinois Administrative Code, Part 405.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Anyone performing Industrial Radiography (either x-ray or gamma) must be
certified by the Department.  Certification as an Industrial Radiographer
is valid for 5 years and may be renewed.  Certification as an Industrial
Radiographer Trainee is valid for 2 years and is not renewable.  An
individual who performs Industrial Radiography without certification is
subject to civil penalties not to exceed $1,000/day the violation occurred
or continues.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for certification must file Form# IL 473-0275, available from
the Department together with proof that applicant has met the requirements
for initial or renewal of certification. Applications are processed in
about 10 working days.  Applicants for certification as an Industrial
Radiographer must have passed the required exam and the required hours of
experience.  Applicants for certification as an Industrial Radiographer
Trainee must document that they have successfully completed an approved
training program.  Each certification will include a "class" endorsement
for the type of radiography authorized:   radioactive materials, radiation
machine, or radioactive materials & radiation machines.  Applicants denied
certification may appeal the decision to the Department.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application Fee - $50.<P>
Application Fee for examination by the Department - $75.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
