<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Low-level Radioactive Waste (LLRW) Generators Annual Survey.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Low-level Radioactive Waste (LLRW) Generators Annual Survey.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Nuclear Safety<BR>
Office of Environmental Safety / Division of Low-level<BR>
Radioactive Waste<BR>
1035 Outer Park Dr.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62704<BR>
(217) 524-6309<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>          
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
420 Illinois Compiled Statutes 20/1-20/24<BR>
Illinois Low-level Radioactive Waste Management Act.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
32 Illinois Administrative Code 620.30
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
All LLRW generators must complete a questionnaire requesting the following
information:  1) the types and quantities of LLRW which were either shipped
for disposal or stored on site during the year in question 2) how LLRW is
being managed (e.g. treatment); and 3) what management alternatives a
generator might use in the future.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
LLRW generators must complete and file a registration application with the
Department. (The Generator Management Section will provide assistance in
completing the registration.)  At the end of every year, a survey is sent
to all LLRW generators and brokers which must be completed and returned by
the following February 1.  The Generator Management Section reviews the
survey and associated information, then bills the generators an assessed
LLRW fee.  This information is put into the Department database and an
annual report is produced from the information gathered.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
When a facility has been identified as being a radioactive materials
licensee or that a possibility exists that a facility either may produce or
possess LLRW, the facility will be subject to low-level radioactive waste
(LLRW) registration and corresponding reporting requirements.  The facility
must also comply with other sections of the regulations concerning
licensure of entities that use radioactive materials in Illinois.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The LLRW fee shall be $50 (or $3/cu.ft. for LLRW stored or $3/cu.ft. for
LLRW shipped for storage, treatment or disposal, whichever is greater).
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
