<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration of persons performing services which detect the presence of
radon or radon progeny.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration of persons performing services which detect the presence of
radon or radon progeny.
</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Nuclear Safety<BR>
Office of Environmental Safety / Division of Environmental Monitoring<BR>
1035 Outer Park Dr.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62704<BR>
(217) 786-7127<BR>
</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III. Statute :</H3>
<DL><DD>
420 Illinois Compiled Statutes 45/1 - 45/3.<BR>
The Radon Testing Act
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 32, Illinois Administrative Code, Part 420.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Persons who perform any service to detect the presence of radon or radon
progeny (decay products) must be registered with the Department.  Included
are persons who place passive sampling devices and those who take
measurements with electronic devices. Persons are exempt who only sell, but
do not place or measure radon sampling devices supplied
by a laboratory.  Individual's must renew registration every 2 years.
Businesses must renew annually.  People who perform such services without
registration are subject to fines from $500 to $1,000.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete  a form provided by the Department and provide
proof that applicant has met education and/or experience requirements for
registration.  If the application is satisfactory, a registration
certificate will be issued in about 10 working days.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Test results must be reported to the client within 45 days after testing,
and registrants must make  the results of testing available for Department
inspection.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG><EM>Individual Registration: </EM></STRONG> Initial or Renewal - $100 (for 2 years)<P>
<STRONG><EM>Business Registration:</EM></STRONG>    Initial or Renewal - $25 (for 1 year)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
