<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Naprapath</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile: </H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Naprapath
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Health Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786	<BR>
Phone  (217) 524-7540<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 63/1-200
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required to practice Naprapathy (generally defined as the evaluation and treatment of persons with connective tissue disorders, by means of connective tissue manipulation, therapeutic and rehabilitative exercise, postural counseling, nutritional counseling, and the use of assistive devices which utilize the properties of heat, light, water, air, or electricity to prevent and alleviate physical disabilities).<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must have graduated from a 2 year college-level program and be a graduate from a curriculum in Naprapathy, both of which are subject to the approval of the Department.  All applicants must pass a written examination before a license will be issued. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Active practitioners of Naprapathy may obtain additional licenses as necessary in order to practice as a Naprapath in more than one location. A license must be displayed in each location where the licensee is to be engaged in the practice of Naprapathy. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Naprapath:	$250<P>
(Temporary):   	    	$250
</DD></DL>

