<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Physician & Surgeon, Temporary Physician, Temporary Physician & Surgeon;
License for Visiting Physician & visiting Professor Physician License for Chiropractic Physician, Visiting Professor Chiropractor and Chiropractic Preceptor Physician</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Physician & Surgeon, Temporary Physician, Temporary Physician & Surgeon<BR>
License for Visiting Physician & visiting Professor Physician License for Chiropractic Physician, Visiting Professor Chiropractor and Chiropractic Preceptor Physician
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Health Services Section Medical Unit<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786<BR>
(217) 524-7530<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 60/1-63 Illinois Medical Practice Act of 1987
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, Subchapter B., part 1285
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
All physicians and surgeons practicing in Illinois must have a License from the Department. The requirement applies to all persons practicing in the State.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must pass a written examination approved by the Department. Applicants must indicate to the Department which category of medicine they intend to practice.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must satisfied education requirements before they are eligible to take licensing exams: Applicants for a license to practice medicine in all of its branches must have graduated from an accredited medical college with a Doctor of Medicine degree, including a total of 6 years of post secondary study with at least 2 academic years of study in the basic medical sciences, and 2 academic years of study in the clinical sciences.<P>

Applicant for a license to practice Chiropractic medicine must have graduated from an approved school of chiropractic with a curriculum of at least 132 weeks in duration after having completed a 2 year course of instruction in liberal arts.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Physician - Surgeon 				$300<BR>
Chiropractor						$300<BR>
Chiropractic Preceptor Physician 		$ 50<BR>
Chiropractic Preceptor Program		$ 50<BR>
Visiting Physician 					$300<BR>
Visiting Professor Physician 			$300<BR>
Visiting Professor Chiropractor 		$300<BR>
Temporary Physician License 			$100<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
