<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Private Security Contractor, Private Security Contractor Agency, Private Security Contractor Agency Branch Office</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Private Security Contractor, Private Security Contractor Agency, Private Security Contractor Agency Branch Office
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786<BR>
(217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes  446/1-299
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, Subchapter b.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required before any person may engage in the business of providing security services in the form of guards, watchmen, patrol services, or any like services to any person, corporation, or association. <P>

An Agency license is required for any individual, firm, association, corporation employing one or more persons to operate a Private Security Contractor business. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application forms are available from Department. Private Security Contractors must pass a written examination approved by the Department.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for Private Security Contractor must be 21, a U.S. citizen and have worked full time as a full-time manager or administrator for a licensed Private Security Contractor or a manager or administrator of a proprietary security force registered with the Department, employing 30 or more persons for three of the five years preceding the date of application, or have worked full time as a supervisor for three of the preceding five years of the date of application for a federal or State (political sub-division) law enforcement agency. Applicants with a bachelors degree in police science or related field, may substitute the degree for 2 of the 3 required years of experience.  Applicants with an Associates degree in police science or related field, may substitute the degree for 1 year of  the required 3 years experience. Also, applicants must obtain liability insurance in an amount of at least $1 million dollars.  <P>

Applicants must show proof of this insurance before a license will be issued.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Private Security Contractor: 		 			   $500.<BR>
Private Security Contractor Agency:  			   $500.<BR>
Private Security Contractor Agency (Branch Office):  $200.<BR>
Agency Employee:  							   $ 55.<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
