<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Professional Service Corporation & Registration for Professional Design Firm</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Professional Service Corporation & Registration for Professional Design Firm
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786<BR>
Phone (217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
805 Illinois Compiled Statutes 10/1-19, 225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 325/23, 225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 305/21
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Individuals or groups of individuals offering services for which a professional license is required may establish a Professional Service Corporation. A License is required from the Department to form a Professional Service Corporation.  Only persons licensed to provide the professional services for which the Corporation was formed may have part in the ownership, management or control of the Corporation. <P>

In the alternative, architects, professional engineers or structural engineers in a partnership or corporation that is not formed under the Professional Services Corporation Act must register with the Department as a Professional Design Firm. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Persons conducting business as a partnership or corporation which is not formed under the Professional Services Corporation should contact the Department for forms to register as a Professional Design Firm. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Before granting a License for either a Professional Services Corporation, the Department will verify that the shareholders, directors, officers, agents, and employees are all licensed to render the particular professional service for which the corporation was formed. <P>

Professional Design Firms must identify to the Department the name of a Managing Agent who will be in responsible charge of the operations of the firm. This Managing Agent must hold a current license in professional Engineering. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration: 	$50.<BR>
Renewal: 	$80.<BR>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
