<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Speech Language Pathologist and Audiologist</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>  I.  Business Requirement Profile:  </H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Speech Language Pathologist and Audiologist
        </DD></DL><HR><H3>
II.  Agency:              </H3>
                               <DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation  <BR>
Licensing & Testing Division              <BR>
Health Services Section                       <BR>
Phone (217) 524-7540                              <BR>
                                                     </DD></DL><HR><H3>
III. Statute:</H3>
                  <DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 110/1-34
                          </DD></DL><H3>
Regulation:                             </H3>
                              <DL><DD>
Title 68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, Subchapter b, Part 1465
                                      </DD></DL><HR><H3>
IV.  Requirement Description:                           </H3>
                                                             <DL><DD>
A license is required to practice as an Audiologist (which is defined as individuals who engage in the application of non-medical methods and procedures for the identification, measurement, testing, appraisal, prediction, habilitation, rehabilitation, or instruction related to hearing and hearing disorder).

A license is required to practice as a Speech-Language Pathologist (which is defined as individuals who are engaged in the application of non-medical methods and procedures for the identification, measurement, testing, appraisal, prediction, habilitation, rehabilitation, and modification related to communication development and disorders of  speech, language, voice, swallowing, and other voice related disorders). 

The Department issues both Audiologist and Speech-Language Pathologist licenses.
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
V.   Approval Process: </H3>
                            <DL><DD>
Applicants for a license to practice as an Audiologist or as a Speech-Language pathologist are required to pass a written examination approved by the Department. Applicants must satisfy qualifying criteria before being allowed to take the examination.  
                                    </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3>
                                                           <DL><DD>
Applicants for both the Audiologist and Speech-Language Pathologist license must have earned a Master's degree in Speech-Language Pathology or Audiology from a program approved by the Department. Applicants also must show proof of 9 months of full-time, supervised professional experience in the field of Audiology or Speech-Language Pathology, respectively.
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
VII. Fees:        </H3>
                       <DL><DD>
Speech-Language Pathologist: $90.<BR>
Audiologist: $90.                    <BR>
Renewal: $100                            <BR>

                                             </DD></DL>





