<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Wholesale Drug Distributor </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all> <H3>
  I.      Business Requirement Profile:
          </H3><DL><DD>
License for Wholesale Drug Distributor 
                       </DD></DL><HR><H3>
II.  Agency:
                                         </H3><DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division             <BR>
Health Services Section                      <BR>
(217) 524-7540                                   <BR>
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
III. Statute:     </H3>
                       <DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 120/1-185
                               </DD></DL><HR><H3>
IV.  Requirement Description:                    </H3>
                               <DL><DD>
Anyone operating as a wholesale distributor of prescription drugs in Illinois must be licensed by the Department.  This license requirement applies for all wholesale distribution into, out of, or within the State of Illinois.

Wholesale distribution of drugs includes, but is not limited to, the following categories; manufacturer, repacker, own-label distributors, jobbers, private label distributors, brokers,      warehouses (including manufacturers' and distributors'), chain and wholesale drug warehouses, independent wholesale drug traders, and retail pharmacies conducting wholesale distributions.
                                       </DD></DL><HR><H3>
V.   Approval Process:                                   </H3>
                                                              <DL><DD>
Application forms are available from the Department.
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:
                  </H3><DL><DD>
The Department requires applicants to submit proof that the following standards are met:<OL><LI> Acceptable storage and handling facilities, <LI> Minimum liability and other types of insurance coverage as required by law, <LI> An adequate security system, <LI> A system of record keeping which ensures accurate tracking for all wholesaling activity for period of  2 years after the disposition of each product, <LI> Provide proof that any persons in charge of wholesale drug distribution, storage, and handling will conduct business using sound financial practices according to Illinois law and <LI> Show proof of sufficient inspection procedures for all incoming and outgoing product shipments. </OL>
                               </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VII. Fees:                                       </H3>
                                                      <DL><DD>
Wholesale Drug Distributor License: $200.

                                                              </DD></DL>





<HR>
