<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License to Operate a (non Illinois based) Collection Agency and Branch Office</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License to Operate a (non Illinois based) Collection Agency and Branch Office
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786	<BR>
Phone (217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 425/1-15. The Illinois Collection Agency Act
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, Subch b, Part 1210
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required before a person, association, partnership or corporation may operate a business of collecting debts for compensation.  <P>

Conducting business without a License is a Class A misdemeanor.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must furnish the names and addresses of all owners; if applicant is a corporation, the names and addresses of all persons owning 10% or more of the stock. Applicants must have an acceptable credit rating and have worked at least one year in the credit field. <P>

Applicants who were officers of a former registrant whose certificate(s) were suspended or revoked without subsequent reinstatement will not be granted a new license.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
All applicants must obtain a surety bond in the amount of $25,000.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Application for new License: 		$75.<P>
Application for license renewal: 	$60.<P>
Duplicate License: 				$20.<P>
Certification of License: 		$20.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
