<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Occupational Therapist License/
Assistant Occupational Therapist License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Occupational Therapist License<BR>
Assistant Occupational Therapist License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Health Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786<BR>
(217) 524-7540<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 75/1-21
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 68 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter VII, Subchapter b, Part 1315
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required to practice Occupational Therapy* or to assist in the practice of occupational therapy under a registered occupational therapist's supervision.<P>

(*Occupational therapists evaluate the performance ability of ill or injured persons to function in daily living. Upon referral from a licensed physician, they administer treatment methods for individuals whom the physician determines to be in need of assistance in reaching a level of functional ability for day to day living.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must be U.S. citizens or lawfully admitted aliens, have completed an occupational therapy program of at least 4 years, leading to a bachelor's degree or its equivalent, and pass an examination authorized by the Department.<P>

Occupational Therapy Assistants must be U.S. citizens or lawfully admitted aliens and have completed an occupational therapy program of at least 2 years, leading to an associate degree or its equivalent, and pass the written examination authorized by the Department. <P>

Qualified applicants must complete and file an application for license on forms provided by the Department.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
In addition to the written examination, applicants for Occupational Therapist must hold a baccalaureate degree in occupational therapy from an accredited institution. Applicants for Occupational Therapy Assistant must hold an associate degree in occupational therapy from an accredited institution. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
License:<P>
<DL><DD>
Therapist: 					$25<P>
Therapy Assistant: 				$25<P>
Occupational Renewals:			$40<P>
Occupational Assistant Renewal: 	$20<P>
</DD></DL>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
