<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration of Esthetician, Esthetician Teacher. License for School of Esthetics</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration of Esthetician, Esthetician Teacher. License for School of Esthetics
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section<BR>
(217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 410/1-1 through 410/4-22 The Illinois Barber, Cosmetology, Esthetics and Nail Technology Act
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required to practice as an Esthetician, Teacher of Esthetics, or operate a School of Esthetics.  Operating as a Esthetician, Teacher of Esthetics, or operating a School of Esthetics without registration or a license from the Department is a Class B misdemeanor for the first offense, Class A misdemeanor for the second offense and a Class 4 Felony for each subsequent offense.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for Estheticians and Esthetician Teachers must pass a written exam. Applications are subject to a preliminary review by a testing service before being scheduled to take the exam. Once a candidate has passed the written exam, the Department will provide forms to apply for a license. <P>

Denial of eligibility to take the exam is usually based on deficiencies in education or experience. Reconsideration may be requested within 35 days of the date of the denial notice by submitting additional or mitigating information. Denials may be appealed by filing suit in the circuit court. <P>

A License for a School of Esthetics may be issued only after the Department has made an on-site inspection of the proposed school.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Estheticians</EM> - Must be at least 16, have a high school diploma or GED equivalent  (or be beyond the age of compulsory school attendance), be a graduate of a licensed esthetics school  (or a barber school approved to teach esthetics) where they completed 750 classroom hours of Esthetics training. <P>

<EM>Esthetics Teachers</EM> - Must be at least 18, have a high school diploma, have completed 500 hours of teacher training from a licensed school of Esthetics or Cosmetology and 2 years of practical experience as a registered cosmetologist or esthetician within 5 years preceding the examination or have completed 1,000 hours of teacher training in a registered school of cosmetology. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application for Licensure:	$25.<P>
Renewal of License:	$40.<P>
License Restoration & Lapsed Renewal	$10.<P>
Duplicate License:	$20.<P>
Certification:  	$20.<P>
License for School of Esthetics: $100.<P>

These fees are in addition to any examination fees.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
