<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration for Nail Technicians, Nail Technician Teachers,
Registration of Nail Technology Schools </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration for Nail Technicians, Nail Technician Teachers<BR>
Registration of Nail Technology Schools 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section
(217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 410/1- /4-22 The Illinois Barber, Cosmetology, Esthetics and Nail Technology Act
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter VII, subchapter b, Part 1175
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration with the Department is required to conduct business as a Nail Technician, Nail Technology Teacher or to operate a School of Nail Technology.  <P>

Operating without a License is a Class B misdemeanor for the first offense, a Class A misdemeanor for the second offense and a Class 4 Felony for each 
subsequent offense.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application forms are available from the Department's office by written request or by calling the Forms Unit at 217/785-0842. The Department requires a written exam for Nail Technicians and Nail Technician Teachers. Applications are sent to the testing service for preliminary review before being scheduled to take the exam. Upon passing the exam, applicant will receive necessary forms to apply for issuance of his/her license. Denial of eligibility to take the exam is usually based on deficiencies in education or experience. Reconsideration may be requested within 35 days of the date of the denial notice by submitting additional or mitigating information. Denials may also be appealed through Judicial Review by filing suit in circuit court. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for Nail Technologists must be at least 16; have graduated from eighth grade and be a graduate of a School of Cosmetology or Nail Technology, approved by the Department and completed a curriculum of 350 hours in the study of Nail Technology extending over a period of at least 3 months but no longer than 2 years. All Nail Technician applicants must pass the Nail Technician examination.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees (in addition to any examination fees):</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application for Licensure		$25.<P>
Renewal of License				$40.<P>
Restoration & Lapsed Renewal fee:	$10.<P>
Duplicate License		        	$20.<P>
Certification of License			$20.<P>
</DD></DL>

