<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration for participation in Professional Boxing or Wrestling contests </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration for participation in Professional Boxing or Wrestling contests 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
100 W. Randolph, Suite 9-300<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 814-4539<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 105/1-26<BR>  
(Professional Boxing and Wrestling Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 68 Illinois Administrative Code 1370
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required to participate as a contestant in a professional boxing or wrestling match.<P>

Participation in an event without the License is a Class A misdemeanor for the first offense, and a Class 4 felony for subsequent offenses. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must be at least 18, be of good moral character, file an application with the Department stating he is not in violation of any federal, State or local laws or rules governing boxing, and provide a physicians certificate attesting that he is physically fit and qualified to participate in boxing matches. <P>

Applications may be denied to applicants for several reasons, including: gambling on an athletic event, participating in a fake boxing match or violations of boxing rules and regulations. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
No assumed named may be used unless registered with the Department along with applicant's correct name, date and place of birth, current residence.<P>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Two year Boxing Contestant fee: $20.<P>
Renewal fee is $20.<P>
</DD></DL>

