<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Medical Assistance Program</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Medical Assistance Program
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Illinois Department of Public Aid<BR>
Provider Participation Unit<BR>
P.O. Box 19114<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62794-9114<BR>
217/782-0538 or 217/524-7306<BR>
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<dl><dd>
305 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5
</dd></dl><P>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<dl><dd>
140 Illinois Administrative Code 11-14, 16-20, 23, 24, 26, 27, 32, 33
</dd></dl><HR>
<H3>IV. Description:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Providers eligible to participate in the Illinois Medical Assistance Program include physicians, dentists, optometrists, podiatrists, chiropractors, nurse practitioners, registered nurses, physical therapists, occupational therapists, speech language pathologists, audiologists, general, psychiatric, and rehabilitation hospitals, hospices, federally qualified health centers (FQHC), school based clinics, encountered rate clinics (ERC), health kids clinics, ambulatory surgical treatment centers (ASTC), local education agency's, rural health clinics, home health agency's, community health agency's county health departments, certified hospital organized satellite clinics (CHOSC), early intervention centers, pharmacy's, independent laboratories, opticians/optical companies, durable medical equipment/supply, portable x-ray operators, transportation (ambulance, medicar, hospital-based, or non-registered), taxicab/livery companies, alcohol and substance abuse centers and prepaid health (HMO) centers.  Providers may participate in this program indefinitely.  Enrollment in this program may not be approved or may be terminated for non-compliance with the Act.  Enrollment in the program allows a provider to submit claims for services rendered to eligible medical approved clients. <P>
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>V. Approval  Process:</H3>
<dl><dd>
To participate in the Illinois Medical Assistance Program, applicants must complete and submit a "Provider Enrollment Application" to the Department of Public Aid. Ambulance companies, Ambulatory Surgical Treatment Centers, CRNAs, DASA, Home Health Agency's, Hospices, Hospitals, Midwives, Nurse Practitioners, Portable X-Ray Providers, Rural Health Clinics, and Medical Transportation Providers must attach certification, licensure or identification information to IDPA. <P>

All out-of-state applicants must attach a copy of a currently valid licensure/certification form including expiration date.  Hospitals must be certified for participation or accredited by the Joint Commission on the Accreditation of Healthcare organizations if not eligible for Medicare certification. Applications for enrollment are processed within 10 days of receipt by the IDPA.  Applications may be denied if the provider does not meet the participation requirements or if the services rendered are not covered under the medical program. Applicants who have been previously barred or terminated from the program must receive approval from IDPA before they are allowed to participate in the program. <p>
</dd></dl><hr>

<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites, Post-Requisites: 
</H3><dl>
<dt><STRONG>Pre-Requisites: </STRONG><dd> Applicants must submit to a determination of eligibility before becoming eligible for assignment of a provider number. Providers that are required to submit the "Disclosure of Ownership and Control Interest Statement Form" (HCFA 1513) for participation in the Federal Medicaid Program, also must submit a copy of the HCFA 1513 for participation in the Illinois Medical Assistance Program.  Providers enrolled under the Durable Medical Equipment Regional Carrier (DMERC) program also must enroll with IDPA in the same name supplied to the DMERC carrier. <P>

<dt><STRONG>Co-Requisites:</STRONG><dd> Participants in the program are required to comply with all licensing standards. Any rights, benefits and duties through the Medical Assistance Program may not be assigned  without the consent of the Department of Public Aid. Any rights, benefits and duties through the Medical Assistance Program may not be assigned without the consent of the Department of Public Aid.<P>
</dl><hr>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<dl><dd>
None
</dd></dl>





<HR>
