<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Hearing Aid Dispenser License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Hearing Aid Dispenser License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Office of Community Health<BR>
Division of Health Assessment and Screening<BR>
Hearing Aid Consumer Protection Program<BR>
535 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-4733<BR>   
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 50/1 et seq (Hearing Aid Consumer Protection Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 682 (Hearing Aid Consumer Protection Code)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required to sell hearing aids.<P>
 
Fitting, dispensing or servicing hearing aids without a License is a Class A Misdemeanor.<P> 

Licenses must be renewed every two years.<P>  
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file a registration form to take written and practical exams.<P> 

The Department provides applicants with an exam packet/study guide.<P>

Written and Practical exams are held every other month. Applicants are scheduled for the next available exam and notified in writing approximately 2 weeks in advance.<P> 

After successfully passing both the written and all four parts of the practical exam, applicants may apply for a 2-year Hearing Aid Dispenser License by filing an "Application to become a Licensed Hearing Instrument Dispenser". The Department usually takes 3 days to review and application.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Proof of 20 hours of approved continuing education during the previous two years is required for license renewal.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application fee: Initial $35 -- Written exam fee $75<BR>
Permanent license fee $80 -- Written exam late fee $15<BR>	
Permanent License Late fee $80 --  Practical exam (part 1) fee $50<BR>
License renewal $80 -- Practical exam (part 2) fee $100<BR>
License correction fee (each) $10 -- Practical exam (part 3) fee $150<BR>
License status/Verification request $10 -- Practical exam (part 4) fee $200<BR>
Additional / Duplicate copies of license (each) $10<BR>
License reinstatement/Post late fee $50 (for licenses which have expired for more than 90 days but less than 5 years)<BR>
License reinstatement-extended $100 (for licenses which have been expired for more than 5 years)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
