<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Hospice Program License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Hospice Program License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Office of Health Care Regulation / Division of Health Facilities and Programs<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-7412<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
210 Illinois Compiled Statutes 60 (Hospice Program Licensing Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 280 (Hospice Programs)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Hospice Program must be licensed by the Department. License rules involve hospice service plans, physician services, medical direction and quality assurance.  Licenses are valid for 1 year.  Failure to comply with the Act are subject to an administrative hearing, license revocation or  decertification under the (voluntary) Federal Certification Program.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file with the Department a "Hospice Program License Application" together with a "Hospice Service Plan."   A "Hospice Service Plan," includes: identification of administrators responsible for the program, estimated average monthly patient census, proposed geographic service area,  a list of provided services, names and qualifications of service providers, and a description of the program's clinical record keeping system.<P>  

Applications usually take 1 month to process.  If an application is denied, applicants may correct the deficiencies and reapply.  Department inspections of facilities will take place before a license is issued, then annually. Licenses may be revoked or applications denied if the program fails to comply with the Act and the rules.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>Initial and renewal fees:</STRONG> $25 for volunteer hospice, and $100 for full hospice.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
