<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Hospital Licensing Program</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Hospital Licensing Program
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Office of Health Care Regulation / Division of Health Facilities and Programs<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-7412<BR>
TDD: 1-800-547-0466  (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
210 Illinois Compiled Statutes 85  (Hospital Licensing Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 250  (Hospital Licensing Requirements)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The purpose of this License is to assure that hospital environments are safe and meet community expectations.<P> 
 
A permit application must be completed and filed with the Department before establishing a hospital, and a license must be issued before opening, conducting, operating or maintaining a hospital.<P>  

License rules cover areas including hospital administration and planning, medical staff, personnel, laboratory, radiological services, emergency services, nursing services, surgery, recovery and anesthesia services, food service, housekeeping, laundry and physical plant.<P> 

Municipalities may issue licenses.<P> 

Licenses are valid for 1 year.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit all plans for the hospital the Department for review, which usually takes 3 months.<P> 

Applicants must secure a "Certificate of Need"  (CON) from the Illinois Health Facilities Planning Board and submit it to the Department with an "Intent to Establish a Hospital Permit Application".<P> 

If  the Department's evaluation determines that the applicant is fit, willing and able to provide proper hospital services, able to demonstrate adequate financial resources and able to assure hospital operation and maintenance consistent with the public interest, a permit will be issued.<P> 

An inspection of the facility is then performed and if satisfactory, applicant must submit a "Hospital License Application" for Department review.<P>
 
A license will be issued if the Department finds that the hospital complies with the law and rules.<P>   
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3>
<DL><DD>
A CON is required from the Illinois Health Facilities Planning Board before an application may be filed.<P> 

Before construction may begin a hospital must have approval for construction or remodeling from the Department.<P> 

Inspections are conducted as the Department deems necessary.  Hospitals may submit a copy of the Joint Commission On Accreditation of Health Care Organizations survey report in lieu of an inspection.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
