<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Lead Training Course Accreditation</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.    Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Lead Training Course Accreditation
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Office of Health Protection<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Lead Abatement Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson,  Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-5830<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
410 Illinois Compiled Statutes 45/1 et seq. (Lead Poisoning Prevention Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 845 (Lead Poisoning Prevention Code)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Providers of Lead Training may apply  for accreditation by the Department for lead training courses they provide or intend to provide. The Department can accredit training courses for the following disciplines: Lead Inspector, Lead Abatement Worker, and Lead Abatement Contractor/ Supervisor. Applicants for a license may satisfy Department requirements by completing an accredited course. Applicants do not have to be Illinois residents or be trained in Illinois. But out-of-state training provider applicants must meet the same standards and requirements as in-state applicants. Approval as a training provider in any discipline will be valid for the period indicated on the Department approval certificate. (Lead Inspector Training Providers who already hold a certificate with no expiration date, and who satisfy Department Lead Inspector training course requirements, may receive a new certificate with an appropriate expiration date.)  Applications to renew certification as a Training Provider must be made 30 days before current approval expires. (The application will serve as approval pending Department action.)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
New applicants to be Lead Inspector, Worker, or Contractor/ Supervisor Training Providers for the 8-hour/one day refresher, the 24 hour/3 day initial, and the 32 hour/4 day courses must follow Lead Poisoning Prevention Code requirements and file an application for Lead Training Course Accreditation including information on the faculty, course curricula and agenda, training materials, manuals, inventories of equipment, exam materials and methodology, student/teacher ratios, and other additional information or materials as may be required by the Department.  Applicants must identify and describe facilities for both classroom and field practicum training. Application may take 1 month to process. The  most common reason for denying applications is missing or vague information. Renewal applications only must include information on changes in faculty, course curricula and agenda, training materials, manuals, inventories of equipment, exam materials and methodology, student/teacher ratios and information or materials as the Department may require. Failure to meet or maintain instruction levels necessary to maintain instruction levels to train lead inspectors, workers, contractor/ superivors, or contractors in Lead Poisoning Prevention  Code requirements may result in suspension or revocation of approval.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.   Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Instructors should have appropriate academic credentials or field experience in the lead field. Approved training providers should maintain records of student applications, course attendance, exams, and grades for 3 years. Approved training provider must provide the Department with a list of graduates within 30 days. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.   Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
