<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Tanning Facility Licensure</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.    Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Tanning Facility Licensure
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.   Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Division of Food, Drugs and Dairies / Office of Health Protection<BR>
Tanning Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-7532<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
210 Illinois Compiled Statutes 145/1-83 (Tanning Facility Permit Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 795 (Tanning Facility Code)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license from the Department is required to operate an indoor tanning facility.<P> 

Violators may be deemed a "Public Nuisance" and be referred to the local State's Attorney for prosecution.<P> 

Licenses are valid for 1 year.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete and file with the Department a "Tanning Facility Application". <P>

The application takes approximately 6 weeks to process.<P> 

After the application is reviewed for accuracy and all necessary information is submitted, an inspection of the facility is scheduled by the Department The inspection is usually completed within 90 days.<P> 

No facility may operate until after the initial inspection has been completed. If, after the inspection, an applicant is denied a license, applicant may attempt to correct any problems to be reconsidered for licensure.<P> 

Upon successful completion of the inspection, a license is issued.<P>   
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.   Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>Initial application fee:</STRONG> $250.<P>
<STRONG>Annual license fee:</STRONG> $150.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
