<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Water Well License(s)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.    Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Water Well License(s)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.   Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Environmental Engineering Section<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-5830<BR>
TDD: 1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 345/1  (Water Well and Pump Installation Contractor's License Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 915
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required to perform labor and/or services in connection with drilling and sealing water wells and installing or repairing water well pump equipment.<P> 

A water well contractor license is required to drill, modify or seal a water well.<P>  

A water well pump installation contractor license is required to install or repair water well pumps or equipment.<P> 

An unlicensed person may perform services only at the direction and under the personal supervision of a licensed contractor. Licenses are valid for 1 year, from January 1 to December 31.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.   Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must pass a written exam and supply the Department with proof of work experience. Applications for examination as a water well contractor and/or water well pump installation contractor are available from the Department. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>Pre-Requisite:</STRONG>  Applicants must be 18  with at least 2 years experience (420 working days).  Licensed Water Well Contractors must obtain a permit from the Department or the local health department prior to drilling or deepening a water well. Within 30 days after the well is constructed, a report of construction and pump installation must be submitted to the Department or the local health department. Notice must be given to the local health department 48 hours prior to sealing a well.  A Water Well Sealing form must be submitted to the Department or the local health department at least 30 days after the well is sealed.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Water well or water well pump contractor examination fee (including the first year's license): $50. Water well and water well pump installation contractor examination fee (Including the first year's licenses: $80. Renewal fee for either license: $25 each. The renewal fee for both: $35. Water well permit fee for constructing or deepening a well: $100. Reinstatement of either license which has lapsed for less than 3 years is $10 plus all lapsed renewal fees. Reinstatement of both licenses which have lapsed for less than 3 years is $15 plus all lapsed renewal fees. Reinstatement of either license which has expired for more than 3 years is $150 and requires passing the written exam. Reinstatement of both licenses which have lapsed for more than 3 years is $175 and requires passing the written exam. Examination fees must be paid at least 30 days before  the exam.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
