<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Organization License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement  Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Organization License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Racing Board<BR>
100 West Randolph; Suite 11-100<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 814-2600<BR>
TDD:  (312) 814-5039<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
230 Illinois Compiled Statutes, Act 5
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 11, Illinois Administrative Code, Subtitle B, Chapter I, Part 205
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The purpose of this license is to allow the Racing Board to govern Horse Race Meetings by imposing standard conditions and procedures for all facilities.  <P>

Any organization or person who wants to conduct a Horse Race Meeting must apply for an organization license.  <P>

The effective term for an organization license is one year.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applications for an organization license to conduct a Horse Race Meeting in Illinois must be filed at the office of the Board (listed above) no later than 5:00 p.m. on August 31 of the year prior to the year in which the meet is sought. Each applicant should file fifteen (15) copies of the "Dates Application" with the Board. The applications should specifically state the type of license and dates sought to be awarded.<P>

At least thirty (30) days prior to the application deadline, the Board will provide anyone who has requested an application for an organization license and all current organization licensees with notice of a licensing hearing.  The notice shall be made public and will be posted in accordance with rules governing posting of agendas for Board meetings.<P>

The Board will begin reviewing the within 30 days of receiving the application concerning conformity with rules and regulations.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
No organization license will be issued unless, prior to the proposed racing meeting, the applicant obtains the services of a concessionaire licensed by the Board to provide adequate food and drink services for race track patrons or plans to provide these services itself. Applicants must own or lease a racetrack.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Each applicant for racing dates shall deliver to the Board a certified check or bank draft payable to the order of the Board for $1,000. If the applicant applies for racing dates in two (2) or three (3) successive years, the fee shall be $2,000. In addition, each organization licensee must pay a fee of $100 for each racing program on which its daily pari-mutuel handle is ($400,000 - $699,999) and $200 if it is ($700,000 or more).<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
