<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Cigarette Transporter Permit</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:	</H3>
<DL><DD>Cigarette Transporter Permit</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Miscellaneous Taxes Division<BR>
Inventory & Account Control Section<BR>
(217) 785-5851</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:  </H3>
<DL><DD>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes 130/9c. (Cigarette Tax Act).</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:  </H3>
<DL><DD>These permits authorize transportation within Illinois of unstamped, original packages of cigarettes containing more than 2,000 cigarettes in a single shipment.  The requirement most often applies to out-of-state tobacco retailers transporting cigarettes through Illinois.  Transportation without a permit is a Class 4 felony. The vehicle used to transport the cigarettes is subject to seizure and the cigarettes may be confiscated.  A single trip permit authorizes transportation of a single load or shipment.  A multiple trip permit is valid for one year.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:  <H3></H3></H3>
<DL><DD>An applicant must complete:  Form IDR-169 Application for Single Trip Permit to Transport Cigarettes, or Form IDR- 169A Application for Cigarette Multiple Trip Transporter Permit.  The average processing time for these applications is 1-2 days.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3>
<DL><DD>An applicant must provide a copy of a valid out-of-state tobacco retailers license.  Applications for permits or for renewal of permits will be denied for failure to do so.  Permits must be carried in the vehicle during the transportation of cigarettes.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD> There are no fees for permits.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

