<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Motor Fuel Use Tax Annual License Registration & Decals, International Fuel Tax Agreement (IFTA) or Illinois Interstate Motor Fuel Use Tax.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:	</H3>
<DL><DD>Motor Fuel Use Tax Annual License Registration & Decals, International Fuel Tax Agreement (IFTA) or Illinois Interstate Motor Fuel Use Tax.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency: </H3>
<DL><DD> Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Motor Fuel Tax Division<BR>
(217) 785-1397</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:  </H3>
<DL><DD>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes 505.</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation: </H3>
<DL><DD>86 Illinois Administrative Code 1/500.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:  </H3>
<DL><DD><P>A Motor Fuel Use Tax is imposed on interstate carriers operating commercial motor vehicles* on highways in Illinois. There are two Motor Fuel Use Taxes programs: 1.) the International Fuel Tax Agreement (IFTA) and, 2.) the Illinois Interstate Motor Fuel Use Tax.  Illinois based carriers who operate one or more commercial motor vehicles in at least one other IFTA jurisdiction can apply for an IFTA license and decals.  A carrier based in a non-IFTA jurisdiction, who wishes to operate in Illinois, can apply for an Illinois Interstate license and decals.

<P>An Illinois license and IFTA decal allows a carrier to travel in all IFTA jurisdictions and to file a single return with the Department, reporting miles traveled, gallons used and gallons purchased in each jurisdiction.  The carrier then pays the net due, or receives a refund, whichever applies.  An Illinois Interstate license and decal only allows the carrier to travel through Illinois. If a carrier qualifies as an IFTA or Illinois Interstate licensee but does not wish to participate in either program, a single trip permit (valid for 72 hours) must be obtained from the Department or from a wire service to travel through Illinois.

<P>Operating a commercial motor vehicle in Illinois without displaying a valid motor fuel use tax license, a decal, or a single trip permit, is a petty offense. A commercial motor vehicle found operating in Illinois without registering and securing a motor fuel use tax license or single trip permit is subject to a penalty of $1,000. Operating as a motor carrier without a valid motor fuel use tax license or a single trip permit is a Class A misdemeanor, and each subsequent offense is a Class 4 felony.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Applicants for a Motor Fuel Use Tax license and decals must complete and file application Form # MFUT-12 with the Department.  Licenses and decals are valid for a maximum of one year, from January 1 through December 31.  Applications for licenses and decals are processed in approximately two weeks, but may take longer during renewal season (October through February).  Carriers may be required to file a bond if they have failed to pay taxes, file timely reports with the Department, or an audit indicates it is appropriate to protect the interests of member jurisdictions.  Common reasons for denial of licenses are if the carrier:  Is revoked in Illinois or another jurisdiction, the application is not signed by an owner or corporate officer, has failed to file returns, has a balance due of over $50.00.  Carriers may appeal denial of an application.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Carriers must file a quarterly return.  Form (MFUT-15) with Fuel Summaries must be completed by Illinois IFTA carriers.  Form (MFUT-16) must be completed by Illinois Interstate Carriers.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>

<DL><DD><P>There are no application or renewal fees.  However, the fee for decals is $3.75 per set for each calendar year.  Checks must be made payable to the Illinois Department of Revenue.

<P>*A commercial motor vehicle is defined as: Having two axles and a gross weight or registered gross weight exceeding 26,000 lbs.; having three or more axles regardless of weight, or a vehicle used in combination when the weight of such combination exceeds 26,000 lbs. gross weight or registered gross weight.

<P>Exempted from this definition in Illinois are:  motor vehicles operated by the State of Illinois or the United States, recreational vehicles, school buses, commercial motor vehicles operated solely within the State of Illinois.  (Exempted under the International Fuel Tax Agreement are:  Recreational vehicles.)</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
