<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Non-Beverage User Permit</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:	</H3>
<DL><DD>Non-Beverage User Permit</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Miscellaneous Taxes Division<BR>
Registration & Returns Processing Section<BR>
(217) 782-7610</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute: </H3>
<DL><DD>235 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/1-1 et seq. (Illinois Liquor Control Act)</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:  </H3>
<DL><DD><P>This permit authorizes the tax-free purchase of alcoholic liquors from manufacturers or importing distributors by persons, firms, corporations, etc.  holding a valid Non-Beverage Users License issued by the Liquor Control Commission.  The alcoholic liquor authorized for purchase by this permit is unfit for beverage purposes and is used in medicines, research, antiseptics, flavoring extracts, scientific and chemical products.

<P>Typical applicants for this permit are bakeries, hospitals, college science departments, etc.  The permit is valid for the purchase of the same number of gallons of liquor as is authorized by the licensee's Class of the Non- Beverage Users License, issued by the Liquor Control Commission.  Permits are valid for 15 days from the issue date.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD><P>Applicants must complete and file Form RL-4, Application for Permit to Purchase Alcoholic Liquors Without Payment of Illinois Alcoholic Liquor Tax under Non-Beverage User's License Average processing time for the application is one week.  Upon approval of the application, the Department will issue a permit which entitles the holder to purchase the number of gallons stated on the permit.

<P>A common reason for denial is applicant's request for more gallons than authorized by its class of the Non-Beverage Users License, issued by the Liquor Control Commission.  If the application is denied, applicant may re- apply.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3>
<DL><DD>The applicant must hold a Non-Beverage Users License from the Liquor Control Commission.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>The Department of Revenue has no fee for the permit, but the Liquor Control Commission charges license fees that vary with the class of the license.</DD></DL>

<HR>
